messages.message:
1. We are planning to get rid of all static/shared credentials for instabase-dev account. Please use your own credentials to login to instabase-dev. Session timeout is set at 10 hours. 
If you have a IAM role for your cluster, we can assign permissions to your cluster directly. I will need the required permissions
@Ashish

Actually, since it's cross-account (instabase-test => instabase-dev), we need:

```{
  "Version": "2008-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "AllowCrossAccountPullPush",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<AccountA-ID>:role/eks-node-role"
      },
      "Action": [
        "ecr:BatchCheckLayerAvailability",
        "ecr:GetDownloadUrlForLayer",
        "ecr:BatchGetImage",
        "ecr:GetAuthorizationToken",
        "ecr:PutImage",
        "ecr:InitiateLayerUpload",
        "ecr:UploadLayerPart",
        "ecr:CompleteLayerUpload"
      ]
    }
  ]
}```
